node.text:
Singapore Opens Quarantine Free Travel For Vaccinated From Germany⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Singapore is opening up quarantine-free travel to fully vaccinated individuals from Germany and Brunei. The restrictions placed on travelers from Germany and Brunei are set to be relaxed on September 8th, but strict rules will still apply for those taking advantage of the scheme.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Lufthansa⁠
⁠

node.text:
Russian Airlines Eye More Destinations In Latin America⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
According to recent reports, five Russian airlines - Aeroflot, Royal Flight, Nordwind Airlines, Pegas Fly, and Azur Air - are eyeing more destinations in Latin America. The future destinations are cities in Mexico, the Dominican Republic, Brazil, and Venezuela. What else do we know? Let’s investigate further.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠

node.text:
American Airlines Bans Alcohol On Flights Until Next Year⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
For passengers who enjoy an inflight tipple on their flight, they’ll have to wait a little longer to buy a drink on American Airlines. Following its ban of inflight alcohol sales back in June, the airline has today revealed that it will extend this ban until January 2022, in line with the new date for the federal mask mandate lifting.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Vincenzo Pace | Simple Flying | @jfkjetsofficial⁠
⁠

node.text:
Wow: FAA Fines For Unruly US Passengers Top $1 Million⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
The U.S. Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) has today proposed over $500,000 in fines against 34 passengers, taking its total for the year to over $1 million. In a year that has seen many high-profile onboard incidents, the FAA has cracked down heavily on unruly passengers since implementing its “zero tolerance” policy.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠
⁠

node.text:
National Aviation Day: Win Flying Free Flying Lessons With App In The Air⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
August 19th is a special day for aviation enthusiasts. It’s the official birthday of aviation giant Orville Wright – one half of The Wright Brothers, the American aviation pioneers credited with inventing, building, and flying the world’s first successful motor-operated airplane. The day was officially named ‘National Aviation Day’ by Franklin D Roosevelt in 1939, and the United States, along with frequent flyers and aeronautic lovers from all around the world, have celebrated the development of aviation on this day every year since.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Jake Hardiman - Simple Flying⁠
⁠

node.text:
Epic Journey: 2 SAS A320neo Operate 9 Hour Flights To Pakistan⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Two little A320neos belonging to SAS have undertaken a mammoth journey across the continents. The two aircraft flew from Denmark to Islamabad on Monday as part of an evacuation effort by the Danish government. Both planes flew for more than nine hours to make the trip.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Airbus⁠

node.text:
Kabul International Airport Reopens On A Limited Basis⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Kabul’s Hamid Karzai International Airport has reopened on a limited basis, according to reports. The civilian side of the airport had been closed until further notice after it was breached by desperate Afghanis seeking to escape the country as the Taliban claimed control of the country’s capital this weekend.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠

node.text:
American Airlines Key For The World’s Longest Airbus A319 Routes⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
This week, the world’s longest A319 route is deep within Russia, with the 3,021-mile service taking up to about six and a half hours. But it is the US that is reigns supreme, helped by American Airlines having more routes in the top-15 than any other airline. The US features nine times in all, led by LATAM Peru’s Lima-Orlando.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠

node.text:
David Neeleman: Breeze Airways Is Here To Stay⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
In a vote of confidence for Breeze Airways, the startup has closed a $200 million Series B funding round. Led by funds and accounts managed by BlackRock and Knighthead Capital Management, LLC., the airline is getting ready for expansion in the winter and fall with the arrival of the first Airbus A220s. Simple Flying spoke with David Neeleman, Founder of Breeze Airways, about the funding and the carrier’s future. In Mr. Neeleman’s own words, Breeze Airways is here to stay.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠

node.text:
Ryanair Branded 'Evil' For Barring Kiwi.com Passengers From Flights⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Ryanair has been branded 'evil' by online travel firm Kiwi.com after the airline revealed it would stop allowing passengers who had booked tickets from the company access to its aircraft. The move comes roughly a year after the Irish low-cost carrier started advising customers that they should only book directly with the airline.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠

node.text:
Prosecution On The Table For Former Uganda Airlines Management⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Uganda’s President Yoweri Museveni has ordered the dissolution of the board of directors for Uganda Airlines. The move comes following a widespread investigation that revealed issues of corruption, mismanagement, and collusion. President Museveni has ordered the IGG to consider prosecuting some of these officials.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠

node.text:
Lufthansa Sends An Airbus A340 To Help The Afghanistan Evacuation⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Lufthansa is helping to evacuate people from Afghanistan with one of its Airbus A340 aircraft. The German government has chartered the flights. The German flag carrier’s aircraft aren’t flying into Afghanistan but instead collecting people removed from the country to Qatar and Uzbekistan by the German military. ⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
